        <h3>The History &amp; The Name</h3>

        <p>
          Muhibbain founded and originally fronted by <em>Erwan</em> as a solo outfit, is now a duo, when
          <em>Abdul Mutalib Nahar @ Adib</em> (Fabulous Cats) accepted Erwan's invitation to join Muhibbain in mid 2013.
          Now Erwan and Adib call themselves, <em>The Muhibbain</em>.</p>

        <img class="tm-white" src="/assets/img/themuhibbain-white-480.jpg" alt="The Muhibbain. Erwan &amp; Adib.">

        <p>
          The Muhibbain, or more accurately, Muhibbain is an Arabic name taken from the
          Arabic root word <em>Hubb (حب)</em>, which means love and hence serves as the
          fundamental principal and overall drive as 'lovers' in spreading love.</p>

        <h3>Adib's Joining</h3>

        <p>
          According to Erwan, the timing of Adib's involvement as a Muhibbain couldn't
          be more perfect as both Erwan and Adib share the same mision and vision and
          compliment each other on and off the stage well. This, according to Erwan also,
          is crucial in their journey as The Muhibbain.</p>
      </article>

      <article lang="ms">
        <p class="date">05 Nov 2014</p>

        <h3>Sejarah &amp; Nama</h3>

        <p>
          Muhibbain yang mulanya ditubuhkan dan dianggotai oleh Erwan, telah berubah wajah
          apabila pertambahan seorang lagi anggota iaitu Abdul Mutalib Nahar @ Adib (The Fabulous
          Cats dan Almawlid) pada pertengahan tahun 2013. Kini, Muhibbain mahu dikenali
          sebagai The Muhibbain.</p>

        <img class="tm-white" src="/assets/img/themuhibbain-white-480.jpg" alt="The Muhibbain. Erwan &amp; Adib.">

        <p>Nama The Muhibbain digarap dari perkataan Arab, Hubb yang membawa erti cinta,
          seterusnya memberikan maksud keseluruhan penubuhan kumpulan itu untuk
          membawa erti ‘pencinta’ kepada para pendengar dan pengikut mereka iaitu cinta
          sebenar kepada Allah SWT dan juga kekasihNya, Rasulullah SAW.</p>

        <h3>Adib Menyertai</h3>

        <p>
          Menurut Erwan, ketua Kumpulan The Muhibbain, penyertaan Adib sangat bertepatan
          dengan matlamat penubuhan kumpulan apabila mereka berkongsi misi dan visi yang
          sama dalam menyampaikan mesej positif kepada semua pihak tanpa mengira
          golongan dan peringkat.</p>
      </article>
